Add a per-extension reload method to `ExtensionManager` that recompiles a single extension and returns structured results. This enables targeted hot reload without re-scanning all extensions.

## File: `apps/server/src/services/extensions/extension-manager.ts`

Add the result type:

```typescript
/** Result of reloading a single extension. */
export interface ReloadExtensionResult {
  id: string;
  status: ExtensionStatus;
  bundleReady: boolean;
  sourceHash?: string;
  error?: {
    code: string;
    message: string;
    errors?: Array<{
      text: string;
      location?: { file: string; line: number; column: number };
    }>;
  };
}
```

Add the method to the `ExtensionManager` class:

```typescript
/**
 * Reload a single extension: recompile and update its record.
 * Used for per-extension hot reload when the agent edits one extension.
 *
 * @param id - Extension identifier
 * @returns Structured reload result for the single extension
 */
async reloadExtension(id: string): Promise<ReloadExtensionResult> {
  const record = this.extensions.get(id);
  if (!record) {
    throw new Error(`Extension '${id}' not found`);
  }

  // Recompile the extension
  const compileResult = await this.compiler.compile(record);

  if ('error' in compileResult) {
    record.status = 'compile_error';
    record.error = {
      code: compileResult.error.code,
      message: compileResult.error.message,
      details: compileResult.error.errors.map((e) => e.text).join('\n'),
    };
    record.sourceHash = compileResult.sourceHash;
    record.bundleReady = false;

    return {
      id,
      status: 'compile_error',
      bundleReady: false,
      sourceHash: compileResult.sourceHash,
      error: {
        code: compileResult.error.code,
        message: compileResult.error.message,
        errors: compileResult.error.errors,
      },
    };
  }

  // Compilation succeeded
  record.status = 'compiled';
  record.sourceHash = compileResult.sourceHash;
  record.bundleReady = true;
  record.error = undefined;

  return {
    id,
    status: 'compiled',
    bundleReady: true,
    sourceHash: compileResult.sourceHash,
  };
}
```

## Behavior Details

1. Look up the extension record via `this.extensions.get(id)`. Throw if not found.
2. Call `this.compiler.compile(record)` to recompile. The compiler reads the source file fresh from disk and computes a new content hash. If the hash matches a cached bundle, compilation returns instantly (cache hit).
3. Update the record's status, sourceHash, bundleReady, and error fields based on the compile result.
4. If compilation succeeds, clear any previous error on the record.
5. Return structured result. The caller (MCP tool handler) is responsible for broadcasting the SSE event after this method completes.

## Difference from `reload()`

The existing `reload()` method re-discovers ALL extensions from disk and recompiles ALL enabled ones. `reloadExtension(id)` skips the discovery step and only recompiles the single specified extension. This is faster and preserves state in other extensions.

## Error Handling

- Unknown extension ID: throws `new Error(\`Extension '${id}' not found\`)`
- Compilation failure: returns the result with `status: 'compile_error'` and structured error array with file, line, column, text
- Filesystem read failure during compilation: the compiler handles this internally and returns it as a compilation error

## Acceptance Criteria

- `reloadExtension(id)` compiles only the specified extension
- Returns `ReloadExtensionResult` with status, bundleReady, optional sourceHash and error
- Compilation errors include structured error array with `text` and optional `location` (file, line, column)
- Throws when extension ID is not found
- Updates the in-memory `ExtensionRecord` with the compilation result
- Clears previous error when compilation succeeds
- `pnpm typecheck` passes

Add the `reload_extensions` MCP tool handler to `extension-tools.ts` and register it in `mcp-server.ts`. This tool recompiles and reloads extensions, supporting both all-extension reload and single-extension targeted reload.

## File: `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/mcp-tools/extension-tools.ts`

```typescript
/**
 * Handler factory for `reload_extensions` â€” recompile and reload extensions.
 * With no arguments, reloads all. With an `id`, reloads only that extension.
 */
export function createReloadExtensionsHandler(deps: McpToolDeps) {
  return async (args: { id?: string }) => {
    const manager = requireExtensionManager(deps);
    if (!manager) {
      return jsonContent({ error: 'Extension system is not available' }, true);
    }

    try {
      if (args.id) {
        // Single-extension reload
        const result = await manager.reloadExtension(args.id);
        return jsonContent({
          results: { [result.id]: result },
          summary: {
            total: 1,
            compiled: result.status === 'compiled' ? 1 : 0,
            errors: result.status === 'compile_error' ? 1 : 0,
          },
        });
      }

      // Full reload
      const extensions = await manager.reload();
      const results: Record<string, unknown> = {};
      let compiledCount = 0;
      let errorCount = 0;

      for (const ext of extensions) {
        const entry: Record<string, unknown> = {
          status: ext.status,
          bundleReady: ext.bundleReady,
        };
        if (ext.error) {
          entry.error = ext.error;
          errorCount++;
        }
        if (ext.status === 'compiled') {
          compiledCount++;
        }
        results[ext.id] = entry;
      }

      return jsonContent({
        results,
        summary: {
          total: extensions.length,
          compiled: compiledCount,
          errors: errorCount,
        },
      });
    } catch (err) {
      return jsonContent(
        { error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Failed to reload extensions' },
        true
      );
    }
  };
}
```

